06/09/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- As expected, parliament approved Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan's new government on Wednesday (September 5th).
After the vote, he promised that the government would defend democracy, treat all citizens as equals and protect Turkey's security.
Visiting British Foreign Secretary David Miliband, meanwhile, reiterated his government's strong support for Turkey's EU membership bid.
He met with Turkish counterpart Ali Babacan, Erdogan and newly elected President Abdullah Gul.
(AFP, AP, Reuters, BBC, Zaman, Sabah, Radikal - 06/09/07;
NTV, AFP - 05/09/07)
